    "rawSections": {
      "HEADER": [
        "Home > Gamemastering > Bestiary > Magical Beasts > Rabbit Family > Leaf Bunny Table of Contents A wild rabbit that usually lives in the grass. A strict herbivore, it carries around grass wherever it goes. Despite being small for a monster it has powerful front teeth which it can use to cause great damage. As cute as they might appear, if one should come across one they should dispatch it as soon as possible. Given that they love munching on nutritious grass, it is common to find these leaf bunnies in areas with rich soil. Leaf Bunny (CR 1/4)",
        "XP 100",
        "N Tiny Animal",
        "Init +3; Senses Low-light vision; Perception +1"
      ],
      "DEFENSE": [
        "AC 15, touch 15, flat-footed 12 (+3 dex, +2 size)",
        "hp 3 [7] (1d8-1)",
        "Fort +1, Ref +5, Will +1",
        "Weakness Fire"
      ],
      "OFFENSE": [
        "Speed 50 ft.",
        "Melee Bite -2 (1d3-4)",
        "Special Attacks Carrot",
        "Space 2.5 ft.; Reach 0 ft."
